/target
/release
Cargo.lock
*.log
*.png
!resources/template/**/*.png
!resources/guide/**/*.png
!tests/fixtures/**/*.png
tmpclaude-*
/debug/

# Python (debug/calibration tooling under scripts/)
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
.uv/

.env*

# Cloudflare Worker local artifacts (infra/worker)
.wrangler/

# Release signing keys (per docs/EXECPLAN_RELEASE_SIGNING.md). The minisign
# SECRET key must never be committed; the canonical copy lives outside the
# repo (~/.minisign/gakumas.key). These patterns are defence-in-depth in case
# a key file is ever generated inside the tree. The PUBLIC key is safe (it is
# embedded in src/update/endpoints.rs), but we don't track it as a file.
*.key
*.minisign.pub
gakumas-minisign.pub
minisign.key
